verience - over fitting - high-variance model tries to learn every single detail of its specific training set (including the random noise), it is extremely sensitive.
Change one tiny thing in the training data, and the model completely changes its logic. This is why it performs so well on training data but falls apart the moment it sees new, unseen data.


